<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-29T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="732" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/904</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-29T19:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>4270. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 104. Your No. 103, Embassy 3942, May 21, 4 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d732fn1">Not printed; for a fuller explanation of the
                                    plan in question, see telegram from the Chargé in Great Britain,
                                    No. 10390, June 3, <hi rend="italic">infra.</hi>
                                </note> We approve in principle the plan for creation of
                                inter-Allied committee at Madrid to consider proposed imports from
                                Associated nations and to cooperate closely with Inter-Allied Bureau
                                of Purchases, Madrid, so that status of applications to export from
                                Spain may be considered in connection with Spanish requests for
                                imports into Spain from Associated nations. We note that the plan as
                                set out in your cable does not appear to contemplate Italian
                                representative. We feel that for political reasons Italy should be
                                given an opportunity to name a representative on any inter-Allied
                                committee set up in Spain. We are cabling <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> and
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1">Chadbourne</persName> our views as above set out and are
                                authorizing <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName>, if he can appropriately do so, to discuss
                                the matter with the British with a view to obtaining their adherence
                                to the plan.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>